This software's Bosch BME280 sensor handling is based on Bosch's official BME280 Sensor API,
originally created and maintained by Bosch Sensortec (copyright (c) 2016-2023), published and available at:
https://github.com/boschsensortec/BME280_SensorAPI

BME280 Sensor API is distributed under the BSD-3-Clause License, which is included in the original repository:
https://github.com/boschsensortec/BME280_SensorAPI/blob/master/LICENSE
and in this repository in the `LICENSE_BME280` file.

Bosch's `i2c.h` (C++) BME280 usage pattern has been re-implemented using ESP-IDF's `i2c_master.h` (C).
This reimplementation is an independent work and does not include any direct copying
of the vendor's original source code, and it is distributed under the terms of the MIT License.

Bosch Sensortec retains the copyright to the original BME280 Sensor API sample code.


This software's Texas Instruments TMP117 sensor handling is based on SparkFun TMP117 Arduino Library
originally created and maintained by SparkFun Electronics (copyright (c) 2016-2023), published and available at:
https://github.com/sparkfun/SparkFun_TMP117_Arduino_Library 

SparkFun TMP117 Arduino Library is distributed under the MIT License, which is included in the original repository:
https://github.com/sparkfun/SparkFun_TMP117_Arduino_Library/blob/master/LICENSE.md
and in this repository in the `LICENSE_TMP117` file.

SparkFun's `i2c.h` (C++) TMP117 I2C usage pattern has been re-implemented using ESP-IDF's `i2c_master.h` (C).
This reimplementation is an independent work and does not include any direct copying
of the vendor's original source code, and it is distributed under the terms of the MIT License.

SparkFun Electronics retains the copyright to the original SparkFun TMP117 Arduino Library sample code.


This software includes a reimplementation of communication patterns for the AHT20 temperature and humidity Sensor,
based on concepts and methods published in the sample code provided by Guangzhou Aosong Electronics Co., Ltd. for STM32 microcontrollers.

The original sample code can be accessed via: the vendor's product page: http://www.aosong.com/en/products-32.html
and sample code (RAR archive) download link: http://aosong.com/userfiles/files/software/AHT20-21%20DEMO%20V1_3(1).rar

This reimplementation is an independent work and does not include any direct copying
of the vendor's original source code, and it is distributed under the terms of the MIT License.

Guangzhou Aosong Electronics Co., Ltd. retains the copyright to the original sample code.


This software also uses the ESP-IDF framework,
created and maintained by Espressif Systems (Shanghai) Co., Ltd., published and available at:
https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf  

ESP-IDF is distributed under the Apache License 2.0, which is included in the original repository:
https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf/blob/master/LICENSE
and in this repository in the `LICENSE_ESP-IDF` file.

The parts of the ESP-IDF framework's code is used for building my own work.

Espressif Systems (Shanghai) Co. Ltd. retains the copyright to the original ESP-IDF framework.


